Three people, including a two-year-old girl, were injured when a train collided with a car at the Jackaroo crossing in Witbank, Mpumalanga, on Tuesday. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said emergency services arrived at the scene shortly after 10am. The car was found a few metres from the railway tracks. Meiring said a man, a woman and a two-year-old girl were found sitting outside the vehicle. The man and woman sustained moderate injuries, while the two-year-old girl sustained numerous injuries and was in a critical condition. They were transported to a nearby hospital.